---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Colophon"
  subtitle="How this site is built."
  activeNav=""
>
  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <p>
      Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>
      and <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind CSS</a>,
      hosted on <a href="https://netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Netlify</a>.
      Everything is statically generated — no server, no database. The few interactive
      pieces (search, command palette) use Astro's Islands architecture so they hydrate
      independently without loading a full framework.
    </p>

    <p>
      Typography is Inter for UI and headings, Source Serif 4 for long-form reading,
      and JetBrains Mono for code. Search is handled by
      <a href="https://pagefind.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pagefind</a>,
      which builds its index at compile time so there is nothing to load at runtime.
      Publications are parsed from BibTeX.
    </p>

    <p>
      The source is on <a href="https://github.com/itgall/My-Personal-Website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
